(96, 1, '2012-08-18 08:50:52', '2012-08-18 08:50:52', 'At Genius Works we believe the models by which leaders navigate the world are not meeting the complexity they face. Therefore, the need to upgrade their modes of operating must shift to meet a changing world. More than ever, leaders require a set of skills that demand them to navigate, approach andÂ meet the needs of their environment with both laser-like will, commitment and follow-through as wellÂ as imagination, empathy, courage and audacity. Leaders are required to make educated decisionsÂ within an exponentially changing landscape of parameters, pressures and responsibilities. To do this,Â they must learn to handle ambiguity whilst knowing who they are and continuously discerning whatÂ matters most. This is no small feat.\r\n\r\nThe latest research from "TheÂ InstituteÂ of the Future" (IFTF) suggests that, moving forward, workplaces will work in new ways. What we perceive to be core competenciesÂ are shifting into areas such as social intelligence, Systems thinking, novel and adaptive thinking as well asÂ design thinking mindsets.\r\n\r\nGenius Works understands the enormity of the task and is passionate about empowering, up-skillingÂ and facilitating this vital capacity within organizations that plan to thrive and that want to remain relevant inÂ the coming years.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Training', 'We train organisations in the core skills that will allow them to  thrive in an ever-changing landscape.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'slide-5', '', '', '2013-04-17 16:39:48', '2013-04-17 16:39:48', '', 0, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/standby/?post_type=portfolio&#038;p=96', 0, 'portfolio', '', 0),
