(383, 1, '2013-01-28 10:02:22', '2013-01-28 10:02:22', '<strong><span style="color: #ffcc00;">Oran Cohen</span></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nKnown as an Imagineer, Oran has the ability to facilitate ideas into reality and has served as an inspiration in innovation and creative strategy to individuals and organizations all over the world. Oran is a passionate business and social entrepreneur, consultant, facilitator, musician, designer and creative strategist.\n\nIn 2009 Oran was selected as one of the most interesting young South Africans by the Mail and Guardian and has been called an emerging young global leader. In 2011 he was chosen as 1 of 50 International Evolutionary Leaders by the Source of Synergy Foundation Non-Profit, â€œEvolutionary Leadersâ€. make link - <a href="http://www.evolutionaryleaders.net/">www.evolutionaryleaders.net</a>\n\nOran has worked and consulted in both private and public sectors and collaborated on specific projects with municipalities and organizations such as Cadbury, Johnson &amp; Johnson (America &amp; Ireland), Standard Bank, Cape Union Mart, Sappi Saicor, Deloitte, the Netherlands Embassy,Â  SABC, Talent Attack, and Raizcorp. In these organisations he facilitated product innovation and ideation, leadership training, strategy, leadership communication skills and creative thinking.\n\nHe is a SETA accredited Facilitator and Assessor. He also trained with Disneyâ€™s Imagineering team in Florida, USA. He has run workshops and interventions in Asia, America, Canada, Africa and Europe. Oran has spoken at the United Nations in 2003 during the International Day of Peace and is now a board member on a United Nations NGO called â€œChildren of the Earthâ€.\n\nOran is the Managing Director and founder of Genius Works Consulting.', 'Oran Cohen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '382-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-01-28 10:02:22', '2013-01-28 10:02:22', '', 382, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/382-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(395, 1, '2013-01-28 10:08:35', '2013-01-28 10:08:35', '<strong><span style="color: #ff9900;">Claire Janisch</span></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nClaire is a sustainability &amp; innovation advisor and biomimicry professional. She is a graduate of and a co-trainer for the international 2-year biomimicry Professionals Program (BPCP). She currently heads up biomimicrySA. Claire works in the areas of strategy, technology &amp; education.\r\n\r\nShe is also a co-creator of the Genius Lab, an experiential learning organisation inspiring innovation and future thinking for organisations and individuals (children and adults). She finds inspiration and innovative solutions to human challenges by emulating organisms and ecosystems that fit in on this beautiful planet in well-adapted life-enhancing ways.\r\n\r\nAs a biomimicry professional she spends her time exploring natureâ€™s technological miracles in diverse ecosystems and shares this new way of viewing and valuing nature through expeditions and workshops â€“ teaching &amp; training professionals, students and scholars. She also dives deeper into research for companies and organisations- translating natureâ€™s innovation and sustainability principles for the design of new products, processes &amp; systems.\r\n\r\nClaire has a MSc in the field of Environmental Process Engineering and has worked across Africa as a consultant in: Environmental Technology, Sustainable Energy &amp; Climate Change, Cleaner Production, Sustainable Urban Design, Integrated Waste Management, Sustainable Agricultural Practices, Eco-labeling, Environmental Management &amp; Environmental Education.', 'Claire Janisch', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '386-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-01-28 10:08:35', '2013-01-28 10:08:35', '', 386, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/386-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(711, 3, '2013-04-17 16:59:01', '2013-04-17 16:59:01', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Oran Cohen</b>\r\n\r\nKnown as an Imagineer, Oran has the ability to facilitate ideas into reality and has served as an inspiration in innovation and creative strategy to individuals and organisations world-wide. Oran is a passionate business and social entrepreneur, consultant, facilitator, musician, designer and creative strategist. He is a SETA-accredited Facilitator and Assessor. He also trained with Disneyâ€™s Imagineering team in Florida, USA. He has run workshops and interventions in Asia, America, Canada, Africa and Europe. He spoke at the United Nations in 2003 during the International Day of Peace and is now a board member on a United Nations NGO called â€œChildren of the Earthâ€.\r\n\r\nIn 2009 he was selected as one of the most interesting young South Africans by the <i>Mail and Guardian</i> and has been called an emerging young global leader. In 2011 he was chosen as one of 50 International Evolutionary Leaders by the Source of Synergy Foundation Non-Profit. â€œEvolutionary Leadersâ€.\r\n\r\nOran has worked and consulted in both private and public sectors and collaborated on specific projects with municipalities and organisations such as Cadbury, Johnson &amp; Johnson (America and Ireland), Standard Bank, Cape Union Mart, Sappi Saicor, Deloitte, the Netherlands Embassy,Â  the South African Broadcasting Corporation, Talent Attack, and Raizcorp. In these organisations he facilitated product innovation and ideation, leadership training, strategy, leadership communication skills and creative thinking.\r\n\r\nOran is the Managing Director and founder of Genius Works Consulting.', 'Oran Cohen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '382-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-04-17 16:59:01', '2013-04-17 16:59:01', '', 382, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/382-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
