 #00ccff;">Leading and Shaping the Story</span></b></h3>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">The workshop will take theÂ participantsÂ through a journey of uncovering Story from different angles. It will offer an introductionÂ to the power ofÂ storyÂ and story-telling spanning different ways from ancient stories to how stories mobilise, lead, transform and empower brands as well as how leaders can learn to tell their story with imagination in order to allow the the power of story to becoming an ally in the leadership process. In partnership with Dorian Haarhof (SA''s leading organisational storyteller).\r\n<b>Cape Town:Â </b>7<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 8<sup>th</sup>Â MayÂ  Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 11<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 12<sup>th</sup>Â March</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="padding-left: 30px;"><b>Module 5: <span style="color: #00ccff;">Enrolling the Tribe</span></b></h3>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">How to construct ideas that "stick". How to move from "salesperson" to "partner". How to enroll others into your ideas, create buy-in for new initiatives and co-create visions in teams, organisations, with stakeholders and within communities. A vital skill in today''s world.\r\n<b>Cape Town:Â </b>17<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 18<sup>th</sup>Â AprilÂ  Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 9<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 10<sup>th</sup>Â May</p>\r\nThis Learning Journey will be available to all those with the passion and the desire to learn the new modalities and approaches to innovative leadership. Genius Works is committed to building this literacy and creating community where these ideas can be explored.\r\n\r\n<b><i>Please contact ourÂ teamÂ inÂ JohannesburgÂ atÂ <a href="mailto:louise@geniusworks.co.za" target="_blank">louise@geniusworks.co.za</a>Â orÂ in Cape TownÂ at<a href="mailto:riaan@geniusworks.co.za" target="_blank">riaan@geniusworks.co.za</a>Â for Corporate, NGO and individual rates. Discounts areÂ available for groups and multi-module learningÂ participants.</i></b>\r\n\r\nWishing you a potent, thrilling and