eption governs the way we deal with problems and how to overcome this challenge. Together, we will explore new methods of solution-making, how to develop the ability to see things with new eyes as well as unpack new applicable models of dealing with challenges. Also, we''ll learn cutting edge techniques gathered straight from the Imagineers at Disney.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><b>Cape Town:Â </b>19<sup>th</sup>Â February Â Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 26<sup>th</sup>Â of February</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="padding-left: 30px;"><b>Module 2: <span style="color: #00ccff;">Facilitating Genius</span></b></h3>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">The Skill and the Art of facilitating and extrapolating genius. How to mobilise and facilitate the genius of teams, groups and communities. How to incite, guide and harvest collective wisdom.Â RecommendedÂ for leaders social innovators and managers.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Cape Town:Â </strong></span>20<sup>thÂ </sup>â€“ 21<sup>st</sup>Â February Â Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 27<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 28<sup>th</sup>Â February</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="padding-left: 30px;"><b>Module 3: <span style="color: #00ccff;">Re-Imagining Systems</span></b></h3>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Theories,Â techniquesÂ and applications of how to learn to think and act systemically. How to design systemic engagements within organisations and collaboratives. Introduction to Systems Thinking (Part 1) and Places to intervene in a System (Part 2). This revolutionary program teaches individuals the basics of both Biomimicry as a perception and problem solving tool as well as the latest research in systemic interventions.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><b>Cape Town:Â </b>14<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 16<sup>th</sup>Â MarchÂ  Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 11<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 13<sup>th</sup