(762, 3, '2013-10-10 20:50:25', '2013-10-10 20:50:25', '<p style="text-align: center;"><img class=" wp-image-455 aligncenter" alt="Lead with Imagination Leadership Programme" src="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/LWIHeader.png" width="650" height="200" /></p>\r\nAt Genius Works we believe the models by which leaders navigate the world are not meeting the complexity they face. More than ever, leaders are required to make educated decisions within an exponentially changing landscape of parameters, pressures and responsibilities.\r\n\r\nTo do this, they must learn to handle ambiguity with flexibility and creativity, while continuously discerning what matters most.\r\n\r\nThe Lead With Imagination programme is a multi-module learning journey, which equips leaders with the essential skills to navigate complexity and change. The modules are a collation of techniques, tools and perspectives from around the world.\r\n\r\n<b>Module 1: Thinking Bootcamp</b>\r\n<i>The skills of understanding and solving complex problems.</i>\r\n\r\nThis introductory module looks at how perception is at the heart of almost all problems and develops the participantsâ€™ ability to embody multiple perspectives in order to create effective solutions. Participants are introduced to Creative Problem Solving, Design Thinking and some of the cutting-edge methodologies that are being used to deal with complex problems.\r\n\r\n<b>Module 2: Facilitating Genius\r\n</b><i>How to facilitate and lead creativity and innovation.</i>\r\n\r\nIn todayâ€™s world collaboration is essential. Facilitating Genius is a study in mobilising and facilitating the genius of teams, groups and communities, and how to inspire, guide and harvest their collective wisdom.\r\n\r\n<b>Module3: Re-Imagining Systems\r\n</b><i>An introduction to Complexity and Systems Thinking</i>\r\n\r\nOften when we try to create change or innovation, we expend a lot of energy on taking action in a system without understanding the underlying structures at play. This module brings together Biomimicry and Systems Thinking to understand how to design smarter and more enduring solutions to the problems we face.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5em;">Module 4: Re-Defining the Story\r\n</span></strong><i>Traditional and digital storytelling in the context of leadership.</i>\r\n<h3>Everything is a story; systems, organisations, products, relationships. This module equips participants with the basics of how to lead and shape stories in order to mobilise, lead, transform and empower people and brands.</h3>\r\n<b>Module 5: Enrolling the Tribe</b>\r\n<i>Creating ideas that stick and building a following for change.</i>\r\n<h3>Enrolling the tribe is about moving from â€œsalespersonâ€ to â€œpartnerâ€. Itâ€™s about the art of enrolling others into your ideas, creating buy-in for new initiatives and co-creating visions in teams, organisations, with stakeholders and communities.</h3>\r\n<i>Â </i><b>Module 6: Navigating the Unknown\r\n</b><i>Leadership tools to deal with ambiguity and change.</i>\r\n\r\nIn a constantly changing world, flexibility, spontaneity and accelerated decision making are skills that are becoming indispensable. Navigating the Unknown unpacks the challenges and the approaches to navigating the dancing landscapes we face.', 'Lead with Imagination', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '448-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-10 20:50:25', '2013-10-10 20:50:25', '', 448, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/448-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
