>Modules will include:</b>\r\n<h3><b>Module 1:Â How to Eat an Elephant</b></h3>\r\nIntroduction to Innovation and ideation.Â ParticipantsÂ will learn how perception governs the way we deal with problems and how to overcome this challenge. Together, we will explore new methods of solution-making, how to develop the ability to see things with new eyes as well as unpack new applicable models of dealing with challenges. Also, we''ll learn cutting edge techniques gathered straight from the Imagineers at Disney.\r\n\r\n<b>Cape Town:Â </b>19<sup>th</sup>Â February Â <strong>Â Johannesburg:</strong>Â 26<sup>th</sup>Â of February\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h3><b>Module 2:Â Facilitating Genius</b></h3>\r\nThe Skill and the Art of facilitating and extrapolating genius. How to mobilise and facilitate the genius of teams, groups and communities. How to incite, guide and harvest collective wisdom.Â RecommendedÂ for leaders social innovators and managers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cape Town:Â </strong>20<sup>thÂ </sup>â€“ 21<sup>st</sup>Â February Â Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 27<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 28<sup>th</sup>Â February\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h3><b>Module 3:Â Re-Imagining Systems</b></h3>\r\nTheories,Â techniquesÂ and applications of how to learn to think and act systemically. How to design systemic engagements within organisations and collaboratives. Introduction to Systems Thinking (Part 1) and Places to intervene in a System (Part 2). This revolutionary program teaches individuals the basics of both Biomimicry as a perception and problem solving tool as well as the latest research in systemic interventions.\r\n\r\n<b>Cape Town:Â </b>14<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 16<sup>th</sup>Â MarchÂ  Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 11<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 13<sup>th</sup>Â April<b></b>\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h3><b>Module 4:Â Leading and Shaping the Story</b></h3>\r\nThe workshop will take theÂ participantsÂ through a journey of uncovering Story from different angles. It will offer an introductionÂ to the power ofÂ storyÂ and story-telling spanning different ways from ancient stories to how stories mobilise, lead, transform and empower brands as well as how leaders can learn to tell their story with imagination in order to allow the the power of story to becoming an ally in the leadership process. In partnership with Dorian Haarhof (SA''s leading organisational storyteller).\r\n<b>Cape Town:Â </b>7<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 8<sup>th</sup>Â MayÂ  Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 11<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 12<sup>th</sup>Â March\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h3><b>Module 5:Â Enrolling the Tribe</b></h3>\r\nHow to construct ideas that "stick". How to move from "salesperson" to "partner". How to enroll others into your ideas, create buy-in for new initiatives and co-create visions in teams, organisations, with stakeholders and within communities. A vital skill in today''s world.\r\n<b>Cape Town:Â </b>17<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 18<sup>th</sup>Â AprilÂ  Â <b>Johannesburg:</b>Â 9<sup>th</sup>Â â€“ 10<sup>th</sup>Â May\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h4>This Learning Journey will be available to all those with the passion and the desire to learn the new modalities and approaches to innovative leadership. Genius Works is committed to building this literacy and creating community where these ideas can be explored.</h4>\r\n<b><i>Please contact ourÂ teamÂ inÂ JohannesburgÂ atÂ <a href="mailto:louise@geniusworks.co.za" target="_blank">louise@geniusworks.co.za</a>Â orÂ in Cape TownÂ atÂ <a href="mailto:riaan@geniusworks.co.za" target="_blank">riaan@geniusworks.co.za</a>Â  for Corporate, NGO and individual rates. Discounts areÂ available for groups and multi-module learningÂ participants.</i></b>\r\n\r\nWishing you a potent, thrilling and adventurous 2013!\r\n\r\n<strong>But before you do please help us quote you as best we can by helping us understand your needs by filling in the form below:Â </strong>\r\n<div id="wufoo-z7x3p3">Fill out my <a href="http://geniusworksco