(574, 1, '2013-02-09 13:36:18', '2013-02-09 13:36:18', '<p><a style="font-size: 2.4em;" href="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/LWIHeader.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-455 alignnone" alt="LWIHeader" src="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/LWIHeader.png" width="650" height="200" /></a></p><h4>At Genius Works we believe the models by which leaders navigate the world are not meeting the complexity they face.Â Therefore, the need to upgrade their modes of operating must shift to meet a changing world.</h4><p>More than ever, leaders require a set of skills that demand them to navigate, approach and meet the needs of their environment with both laser-like will, commitment and follow-through as well as imagination, empathy, courage and audacity.</p><p>Leaders are required to make educated decisions within an exponentially changing landscape of parameters, pressures and responsibilities. To do this, they must learn to handle ambiguity whilst knowing who they are and continuously discerning what matters most.</p><p><img class="size-medium wp-image-503 alignright" style="border: 0px; margin-top: 3px; margin-bottom: 3px;" alt="Solving complex problems" src="../wp-content/uploads/2013/02/A_B-203x300.png" width="203" height="300" /></p><p><strong>This is no small feat.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>This year we have set up an exciting leadership learning journey for social change-makers, change agents and ripple makers to assist them to learn the new literacies of what it takes to lead in a world of ever-increasing complexity, ambiguity and change.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The program is called "Lead with Imagination".</strong></p><p>Our aim is to help leaders and social innovators within organisations to learn the new literacies of the tools, paradigms and understandings that are required to Lead with Imagination.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I wanted to share the exciting line-up that we''ll be rolling out this year;</p><p><strong>Modules will include:</strong></p><h3><strong>Module 1:Â <span style="color: #00ccff;">How to Eat an Elephant</span></strong></h3><p>Introduction to Innovation and ideation.Â ParticipantsÂ will learn how perception governs the way we deal with problems and how to overcome this challenge. Together, we will explore new methods of solution-making, how to develop the ability to see things with new eyes as well as unpack new applicable models of dealing with challenges. Also, we''ll learn cutting edge techniques gathered straight from the Imagineers at Disney.</p><p><strong>Â </strong></p><p>_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _</p><h3><strong>Module 2:Â <span style="color: #00ccff;">Facilitating Genius</span></strong></h3><p>The Skill and the Art of facilitating and extrapolating genius. How to mobilise and facilitate the genius of teams, groups and communities. How to incite, guide and harvest collective wisdom.Â RecommendedÂ for leaders social innovators and managers.</p><p><strong>Â </strong></p><p>_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _</p><h3><strong>Module 3:Â <span style="color: #00ccff;">Re-Imagining Systems</span></strong></h3><p>Theories,Â techniquesÂ and applications of how to learn to think and act systemically. How to design systemic engagements within organisations and collaboratives. Introduction to Systems Thinking (Part 1) and Places to intervene in a System (Part 2). This revolutionary program teaches individuals the basics of both Biomimicry as a perception and problem solving tool as well as the latest research in systemic interventions.</p><p><strong><br /> </strong><strong></strong></p><p>_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _</p><h3><strong>Module 4:<span style="color: #00ccff;">Â Leading and Shaping the Story</span></strong></h3><p>The workshop will take theÂ participantsÂ through a journey of uncovering Story from different angles. It will offer an introductionÂ to the power ofÂ storyÂ and story-telling spanning different ways from ancient stories to how stories mobilise, lead, transform and empower brands as well as how leaders can learn to tell their story with imagination in order to allow the the power of story to becoming an ally in the leadership process. In partnership withÂ Halo and the Noose as South Africa''s leading organisational storytellers.<br /> <strong><br /> </strong></p><p>_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _</p><h3><strong>Module 5:Â <span style="color: #00ccff;">Enrolling the Tribe</span></strong></h3><p>How to construct ideas that "stick". How to move from "salesperson" to "partner". How to enroll others into your ideas, create buy-in for new initiatives and co-create visions in teams, organisations, with stakeholders and within communities. A vital skill in today''s world.<br /> <strong><br /> </strong></p><p>_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _</p><h4>This Learning Journey will be available to all those with the passion and the desire to learn the new modalities and approaches to innovative leadership. Genius Works is committed to building this literacy and creating community where these ideas can be explored.</h4><address>** Please note that dates of modules are subject to change andÂ participantsÂ who have bookedÂ will be notified in advance if this occurs.</address><p><strong><em>Please contact ourÂ teamÂ inÂ JohannesburgÂ atÂ <span style="color: #00ccff;"><a href="mailto:louise@geniusworks.co.za" target="_blank"><span style="color: #00ccff;">louise@geniusworks.co.za</span></a></span>Â orÂ in Cape TownÂ atÂ <span style="color: #00ccff;"><a href="mailto:riaan@geniusworks.co.za" target="_blank"><span style="color: #00ccff;">riaan@geniusworks.co.za</span></a></span>Â  for Corporate, NGO and individual rates. Discounts areÂ available for groups and multi-module learningÂ participants or fill in the form below.</em></strong></p><p>Wishing you a potent, thrilling and adventurous 2013!</p><div id="wufoo-z7x3p3">Fill out my <a href="http://geniusworksconsulting.wufoo.com/forms/z7x3p3">online form</a>.</div><p><script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[