</strong>\r\n<h3><strong>Module 1:Â <span style="color: #00ccff;">How to eat an elephant</span></strong></h3>\r\nAn introduction to innovation and ideation.Â ParticipantsÂ will learn how perception governs the way we deal with problems and how to overcome this challenge. Together, we will explore new methods of solution-making, how to develop the ability to see things with new eyes as well as unpack new applicable models of dealing with challenges. Also, we''ll learn cutting edge techniques gathered directly from the Imagineers at Disney.\r\n\r\n<strong>Â </strong>\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h3><strong>Module 2:Â <span style="color: #00ccff;">Facilitating Genius</span></strong></h3>\r\nThis covers thee skill and the art of facilitating and extrapolating genius. Here participants learn how to mobilise and facilitate the genius of teams, groups and communities, and how to inspire, guide and harvest collective wisdom.Â RecommendedÂ for leaders social innovators and managers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Â </strong>\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h3><strong>Module 3:Â <span style="color: #00ccff;">Re-Imagining Systems</span></strong></h3>\r\nTheories,Â techniquesÂ and applications of how to learn to think and act systemically: how to design systemic engagements within organisations and collaboratives, and an introduction to Systems Thinking (Part 1) and Places to intervene in a System (Part 2). This revolutionary programme teaches individuals the basics of both Biomimicry as a perception and problem solving tool as well as the latest research in systemic interventions.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h3><strong>Module 4:<span style="color: #00ccff;">Â Leading and shaping the story</span></strong></h3>\r\nThe workshop will take theÂ participantsÂ through a journey of uncovering Story from different angles. It will offer an introductionÂ to the power ofÂ storyÂ and story-telling spanning different stories from ancient times to now, how stories mobilise, lead, transform and empower brands as well as how leaders can learn to tell their story with imagination in order to allow the power of story to become an ally in the leadership process. The module is presented in partnership withÂ Halo and the Noose as South Africa''s leading organisational storytellers.\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h3><strong>Module 5:Â <span style="color: #00ccff;">Enrolling the Tribe</span></strong></h3>\r\nHere we explore how to construct ideas that "stick"; how to move from "salesperson" to "partner", and how to enrol others into your ideas, create buy-in for new initiatives and co-create visions in teams, organisations, with stakeholders and within communities. A vital skill in today''s world.\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _\r\n<h4>This Learning Journey will be available to all those with the passion and the desire to learn the new modalities and approaches to innovative leadership. Genius Works is committed to building this literacy and creating community where these ideas can be explored.</h4>\r\n<address>** Please note that dates of modules are subject to change andÂ participantsÂ who have bookedÂ will be notified in advance if this occurs.</address><strong><em>Please contact ourÂ teamÂ inÂ JohannesburgÂ atÂ <span style="color: #00ccff;"><a href="mailto:louise@geniusworks.co.za" target="_blank"><span style="color: #00ccff;">louise@geniusworks.co.za</span></a></span>Â orÂ in Cape TownÂ atÂ <span style="color: #00ccff;"><a href="mailto:riaan@geniusworks.co.za" target="_blank"><span style="color: #00ccff;">riaan@geniusworks.co.za</span></a></span>Â  for Corporate, NGO and individual rates. Discounts areÂ available for groups and multi-module learningÂ participants or fill in the form below.</em></strong>\r\n\r\nWishing you a potent, thrilling and adventurous 2013!\r\n<div id="wufoo-z7x3p3"></div>\r\n<script type="mce-text/javascript">// <![