(976, 4, '2016-03-22 08:12:28', '2016-03-22 08:12:28', '<blockquote>'' Design is a behaviour not a department'' - David Milne</blockquote>\r\nNo longer just a tool for product designers, design thinking is being applied as a powerful methodology for thinking through complex challenges and creating novel ideas and possibilities.\r\n\r\nDo you need to design a product, a service, an organisation or a solution? In design anything you will learn how to bring cutting edge Design Thinking into your own environment, This complex problem solving methodology taps into people''s unexpressed needs and desires to create effective, often ground-breaking solutions that delight stakeholders and customers.\r\n\r\nDesign Thinking becomes the foundation for the rest of the <strong>anything</strong> series.\r\n\r\nOutcomes:\r\n\r\nIn design <strong>anything</strong> participants will...\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Create effective, often ground-breaking solutions.</li>\r\n	<li>Learn to apply the most-used methodology for innovation today.</li>\r\n	<li>Go beyond product design - to design behaviour, services, spaces, interactions and cultures.</li>\r\n	<li>Access tools to deeply investigate and think creatively about design challenges.</li>\r\n	<li>Apply Human-Centered Design to design solutions for the people that matter most.</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate the different phases of designing solutions - What is? What if? What Wows? What Works?</li>\r\n	<li>Play with tools for creative ideation and discover frame - breaking Â ideas to prototype and test.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Design Anything', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '932-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-22 08:12:28', '2016-03-22 08:12:28', '', 932, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/932-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(977, 4, '2016-03-22 10:49:30', '2016-03-22 10:49:30', '<blockquote>'' Fail often so you can succeed sooner.'' - Tom Kelley, IDEO</blockquote>\r\nPrototype anything is a fun, messy and interactive dive into the process of prototyping your ideas and potential solutions. This experiential and practical programme offers delegates a trip into the mindset and the methods of designing testable prototypes of products, services,interactions and or/social initiatives.\r\n\r\nPrototype allows you to experiment, receive feedback, fail fast and learn even faster! Expect to roll your sleeves up as you plan and build prototypes. prototype anything gives you a push into the realm of practicing and experiencing real life iterations of your ideas, and brings the promise of innovation to life.\r\n\r\nOutcomes:\r\n\r\nIn prototype <strong>anythingÂ </strong>participants will...\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Learn creative, low-cost ways to prototype and test the underlying assumptions of your solutions.</li>\r\n	<li>Prototype ideas across diverse fields and areas ( products, services, structures, software, social interactions, designs).</li>\r\n	<li>Discover and practice the core principles and behaviour shifts required for safe-to-fail experimentation with far reaching benefits in your work and life.</li>\r\n	<li>Engage more deeply with users, customers and stakeholders, gaining valuable feedback from tangible rapid prototyping.</li>\r\n	<li>Learn to give and receive feedback on a regular basis in different environments; whilst building an experimental, learning mind-set.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'Prototype Anything', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '934-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-03-22 10:49:30', '2016-03-22 10:49:30', '', 934, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/934-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
