),
(988, 4, '2016-03-22 10:12:16', '2016-03-22 10:12:16', '<a href="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/1_GW_-03.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-598"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-598" src="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/1_GW_-03-300x240.jpg" alt="1_GW_-03" width="300" height="240" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>''The universe is made of stories, not of atoms.'' - Muriel Rukeyser</blockquote>\r\nWorking with story and narrative is one of the most powerful, but least utilized methods to lead and create change. Everything we do, say and create is based on a story we are busy living, a story we tell ourselves about how things are and how things must be. These stories are a key to understanding how to innovate and find solutions no one else can see.\r\n\r\nIf we can tap into the story of a team, a consumer or an unmet need that exists in our environments,the opportunities that reveal themselves can be revolutionary. In this module, you will learn to uncover the story, extrapolate its meaning and significance in order to understand where change is possible and how to go about achieving it.\r\n\r\nOutcomes:\r\n\r\nIn storify <strong>anythingÂ </strong>participants will...\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Learn to use story as a lens to understand and unpack complex situations.</li>\r\n	<li>Move beyond story telling to story listening, for deeper influence.</li>\r\n	<li>Explore the patterns and roles that stories draw us into, and how we can transform them.</li>\r\n	<li>Shape and drive the stories that lead to a positive change and culture in your organisation.</li>\r\n	<li>Use story listening to tap into people''s unmet needs, unlocking creativity and passion.</li>\r\n	<li>Unpack the science behind the ''storied brain''and the implications for intervention, learning and leadership.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Storify Anything', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '940-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-22 10:12:16', '2016-03-22 10:12:16', '', 940, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/940-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1022, 4, '2016-03-24 13:30:25', '2016-03-24 13:30:25', '<blockquote><a href="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/download-1.png" rel="attachment wp-att-973"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-973" src="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/download-1.png" alt="download (1)" width="300" height="168" /></a>\r\n\r\n''The best way out is always through.'' - Robert Frost</blockquote>\r\nOften, the biggest challenge when trying to innovate is the way we see and approach the problem. Some problems can be solved - but some must be dissolved through a game - changing shift in our approach and understanding of the possibilities. Dissolve anything is about facing complex problems and uncertainty, head on.\r\n\r\nThe tools and skills of dissolve anything enable you to distinguish between a complicated problem (that usually has one answer) and a complex problem (that requires a fundamental shift in our approach) and then to adapt your approach accordingly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '(dis) solve Anything', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '938-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-24 13:30:25', '2016-03-24 13:30:25', '', 938, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/938-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(989, 4, '2016-03-22 10:17:54', '2016-03-22 10:17:54', '<blockquote><a href="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/download-1.png" rel="attachment wp-att-973"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-973" src="http://geniusworks.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/download-1.png" alt="download (1)" width="300" height="168" /></a>\r\n\r\n''The best way out is always through.'' - Robert Frost</blockquote>\r\nOften, the biggest challenge when trying to innovate is the way we see and approach the problem. Some problems can be solved - but some must be dissolved through a game - changing shift in our approach and understanding of the possibilities. Dissolve anything is about facing complex problems and uncertainty, head on.\r\n\r\nThe tools and skills of dissolve anything enable you to distinguish between a complicated problem (that usually has one answer) and a complex problem (that requires a fundamental shift in our approach) and then to adapt your approach accordingly.\r\n\r\nOutcomes:\r\n\r\nIn ( dis)solve anything participants will...\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Distinguish between a complicated problem and a complex problem and adapt their approach accordingly.</li>\r\n	<li>Uncover and test assumptions inherent in their own perception of a problem.</li>\r\n	<li>Access tools to investigate what is keeping the problem in place and dissolve ''stuckness.''</li>\r\n	<li>Embrace uncertainty while applying tools to transform and work through big issues.</li>\r\n	<li>Learn to systemically map the different aspects that are causing the current situation.</li>\r\n	<li>Learn to address complex problems in new and surprising ways.</li>\r\n	<li>Deepen their understanding of their own biases and their avoidance of uncertainty.</li>\r\n</ol>', '(dis) solve Anything', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '938-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-22 10:17:54', '2016-03-22 10:17:54', '', 938, 'http://geniusworks.co.za/938-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
